john minor wisdom (may 17, 1905 â€“ may 15, 1999), one of the "fifth circuit four", and a republican from louisiana, was a judge of the united states court of appeals for the fifth circuit during the 1950s and 1960s, when that court became known for a series of decisions crucial in advancing the civil rights of african-americans. at that time, the fifth circuit included not only louisiana, mississippi, and texas (its jurisdiction since october 1, 1981), but also alabama, georgia, florida, and the panama canal zone.